text.tspan: Food expenditure as a share of family disposable income, United States,
Food expenditure, differentiated between that consumed at home and away from home (such as restaurants, cafes, colleges,
work etc.) as a share of the average family's disposable income. This does not include alcoholic beverages or tobacco.
Source: United States Department of Agriculture (USDA)
